title: Wichita, Kansas
summary: Wichita (/ˈwɪtʃɪtɔː/ WITCH-i-taw)[9] is the largest city in the U.S. state of Kansas and the county seat of Sedgwick County.  As of the 2020 census, the population of the city was 397,532.[5][6]  The Wichita metro area had a population of 647,610 in 2020.[7]  It is located in south-central Kansas on the Arkansas River.[3]
